[0.000, "o", "If you wish to have an extension loaded automatically, use the following\r\u001b[18d"]
[0.001, "o", "; syntax:\u001b[19;3H"]
[0.001, "o", "\u001b[K\u001b[20d  extension=modulename\u001b[K\u001b[21;3H\u001b[K\r\u001b[22d; For example:\r\u001b[23d;\u001b[K\u001b[24d   \u001b[30m\u001b[43mextension=mysqli\u001b[25;2H\u001b[39;49m\u001b[m\u000f\u001b[K\u001b[26d When the extension library to load is not located in the default extension\u001b[27;3Hdirectory, You may specify an absolute path to the library file:\u001b[K\u001b[28;3H\u001b[K\r\u001b[29d;   extension=/path/to/extension/mysqli.so\u001b[30;3H\u001b[K\u001b[31dNote : The syntax used in previous PHP versions ('extension=<ext>.so' and\u001b[32;3H'extension='php_<ext>.dll') is supported for legacy reasons and may be\u001b[33;3H"]
[0.000, "o", "deprecated in a future PHP major version. So, when it is possible, please\u001b[K\r\u001b[34d; move to the new ('extension=<ext>) syntax.\u001b[35;3H\u001b[K\u001b[36d\b"]
